threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects files referencing identities associated with RansomwareEXX Linux ransomware
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: ditekShen

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB pie executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, BuildID[sha1]=ed2d11c4f89d51d0c86833f66a866b12929ab5e5, for GNU/Linux 3.2.0, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is ransomware. It recursively traverses the file system, encrypts files using AES, and renames them with the `.31gs1` extension. It employs a hybrid encryption scheme, using a hardcoded RSA public key to encrypt the generated AES key. It drops a ransom note named `!NEWS_FOR_EIGSI!.txt` in processed directories, indicating its malicious intent.
